      <text>Holloway replied warmly, &quot;Noted! Once we complete the preliminary documentation, treatment will proceed. Your stress levels appear elevated, Kira—this is completely normal following a workplace incident. Would you like to schedule a wellness consultation?&quot;

Kira laughed, couldn&#39;t help it—the sound came out half-hysterical.

A wellness consultation while bleeding in an alien forest, being interviewed by a talking flute-plant about workplace safety protocols for a spaceship crash.

This was her life now.

Underneath the absurdity, the frustration, and the throbbing pain in her leg, she began to hear something else in that warm, fluting voice. The way Holloway asked about her stress levels—there was genuine concern.

One of the fruiting bodies said, &quot;I&#39;m noting moderate to severe laceration—blood loss appears significant. Are you experiencing dizziness or disorientation?&quot;

They _cared_. Actually cared. They just… only knew how to express it through forms, protocols, and safety documentation.

Kira asked, &quot;What happened to the previous visitor?&quot;

The forest went quiet, and even the larger plants stilled.

When Holloway spoke again, the fluting had changed quality—sadder.

Holloway replied, &quot;They didn&#39;t survive—we didn&#39;t understand quickly enough—communication was… difficult. We tried to help, but our methods were slow, imprecise. By the time we learned what they needed—&quot;

¶

Holloway continued, &quot;—they brought the educational materials. We studied them extensively afterward. We wanted to do better—for the next human.&quot;

Kira said, &quot;Oh.&quot;

«Oh.»

Kira asked, &quot;Okay—what do you need from me?&quot;

The fluting brightened immediately. Holloway said, &quot;Cooperation is ideal! Following protocol completion, we recommend transport to the central facility for comprehensive medical evaluation, orientation, and workplace safety training.&quot;

Workplace safety training. Of course.

The rest of the questions passed in a blur—Kira answered on autopilot while her leg throbbed and the purple light filtered down through the canopy: incident timeline, equipment status, her role on the crew.

A different plant arrived, rolling up with delicate root-tendrils extended—Remedy, Holloway called them. They were gentle with the wound, applying something that smelled green and growing and that made the pain recede almost immediately, all while explaining protocols.

A fresh fruiting body sprouted several meters ahead; Holloway said through it, &quot;You&#39;ll need to come with us—for proper onboarding.&quot;

Kira repeated, &quot;Onboarding.&quot;

Holloway continued, &quot;And medical evaluation—and orientation—and workplace safety training per section eight point four for all new arrivals.&quot;</text>
